==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cadillac
<hw>Ca*dil"lac</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. from
<ets>Cadillac</ets>, a French town.]</ety> <def>A large pear, shaped
like a flattened top, used chiefly for cooking.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[From <ets>Cadillac</ets>, the high-end expensive
line of automobiles made by General Motors, often thought of as the best
American-made automobile.]</ety> <def>The best; -- metaphorical, from
the automobile. Often used in the phrase ⟦ldquo⟧the <ex>Cadillac</ex> of
. . . ⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cadis</ent>⟦br⟧
